---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Motherlabs — Ada"
  description="Between what you mean and what gets built, something gets lost. Ada is the step before building — structured intent that Claude Code reads every session."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="hero-headline">
          Between what you mean<br />and what gets built,<br />something gets lost.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          Not because AI isn't capable.<br />
          Because intent was never structured before building started.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/start" class="btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a href="/ada" class="btn-ghost">What is Ada? &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The documented problem — no label, just facts -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <p>
          Natural language is ambiguous. The same words mean different things
          to different readers. When you describe what you want to build,
          AI picks an interpretation and acts on it.
        </p>
        <p>
          If that interpretation drifts from yours, the drift compounds.
          Every session adds distance between what you originally meant
          and what is being built. By the time you notice, unwinding it
          is harder than starting over.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most tools address this after the fact &mdash; better prompts,
          auto-memory, clearer instructions mid-build. These help.
          They don't fix the root: your intent was never structured
          precisely before building started.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- Ada — what it actually is and does -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <p class="lead">Ada is the step before.</p>
        <p>
          You tell Ada what you want to build. Ada asks the questions
          that surface what you actually mean &mdash; not technical questions,
          questions about what the thing should do and be.
          Then Ada produces the files Claude Code reads at the start
          of every session: <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, agents, hooks.
        </p>
        <p>
          Claude Code's auto-memory records what it observed as it worked.
          Ada records what you intend before it starts.
          One is retrospective. One is prospective.
          They are not the same thing.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result: less distance between what you described
          and what gets built. Not zero distance. Less.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <ol class="pipeline" role="list">
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">You describe what you want to build.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                In your language. At whatever level you think in.
                Ada does not ask about frameworks, libraries, or implementation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Ada surfaces what's ambiguous and asks about it.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                What does this need to do? What does it not?
                Who uses it and how? The minimum set of questions
                needed to resolve what's unclear.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Ada produces the structured context.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, agents, hooks &mdash; files on disk
                that you can read and verify against what you originally meant.
                These are not ephemeral. They persist.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Claude Code reads them. Every session.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                The intent you expressed in step one is in the room
                every time Claude Code opens a file. Not inferred.
                Not reconstructed from memory. Present.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- What you actually get -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <p class="label">What Ada produces</p>
        <div class="artifact-list">
          <div class="artifact">
            <code class="artifact-name">CLAUDE.md</code>
            <p class="artifact-desc">
              The project's semantic document. Claude Code reads this
              automatically at the start of every session.
              It contains what the project is, what it is not,
              and what constraints apply.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="artifact">
            <code class="artifact-name">agents/</code>
            <p class="artifact-desc">
              Specialized agent definitions scoped to bounded contexts
              within your project. Each agent knows its domain.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="artifact">
            <code class="artifact-name">hooks/</code>
            <p class="artifact-desc">
              Pre-tool guards that run before Claude Code takes actions.
              They enforce the constraints from your original intent
              at the boundary where decisions are made.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="artifact-note">
          These are plain files. You can read them, edit them, version them.
          Ada produces them. Claude Code uses them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    <section class="section section--cta">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cta-label">Try it</p>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/start" class="btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a href="/ada" class="btn-ghost">Read about Ada &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .container--prose {
    max-width: 44rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 7rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.12;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn-primary {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-bg);
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    transition: background-color 0.12s ease;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .btn-ghost {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    transition: color 0.12s ease;
  }

  .btn-ghost:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .section p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.375rem !important;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-surface-raised);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* Separator */
  .sep {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    user-select: none;
  }

  /* Pipeline */
  .pipeline {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .pipeline-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pipeline-step:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.75rem;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem !important;
    line-height: 1.4 !important;
  }

  .step-body {
    font-size: 0.9375rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
    line-height: 1.65 !important;
  }

  /* Artifact list */
  .label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-dim) !important;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem !important;
  }

  .artifact-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .artifact {
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .artifact:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .artifact-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .artifact-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
    line-height: 1.65 !important;
  }

  .artifact-note {
    font-size: 0.9rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text-dim) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .section--cta {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .cta-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-dim) !important;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem !important;
  }

  .cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 4.5rem 0 3.5rem;
    }

    .pipeline-step {
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
